Weddings in dreams symbolize commitment, unity, and major transitions. They often appear when you are integrating different parts of yourself or preparing for a significant change.

If you dream of your own wedding, it may reflect a desire for stability or a deeper commitment—either to a person, a goal, or a new identity. It can also symbolize personal growth and emotional readiness.

Dreaming of someone else’s wedding may reflect your feelings about relationships, expectations, or social pressure. You may be evaluating your own desires or comparing your path to others.

A chaotic or stressful wedding symbolizes fear of commitment or anxiety about change. You may feel unprepared or overwhelmed by expectations.

A joyful wedding reflects harmony, hope, and emotional alignment. It suggests that something positive is coming together in your life.

Wedding dreams highlight your relationship with commitment, connection, and transformation.
